    "title": "Generating capacity and peak demand of electricity and gas",
    "tablenote": [
      "1 terajoule = 1012joules.  1 megawatt = 106watts.",
      "For Electricity: Refers to the average of the daily maxima during the year. For Gas: Refers to the maximum installed generating capacity, as of end of year.",
      "Electricity companies' peak demands in a year do not necessarily occur at the same time. As a broad indicator, the aggregate peak demand is taken to be the arithmetic sum of individual peak demands of the two electricity companies.  As for gas company, peak demand in a year refers to the figure of the day with peak demand.",
      "Electricity and gas production includes electricity and gas imported from Chinese Mainland (if any).",
      "\"Annual production for the year, measured in terajoule\" divided by \"Installed capacity, measured in terajoule per day x 365 (or 366)\" times 100%.",
      "\"Annual production for the year, measured in terajoule\" divided by \"Peak demand within the year, measured in terajoule per day x 365 (or 366)\" times 100%."
    ],
